    "The Ape210K dataset consists of 210K mathematical problems designed for the elementary school level in China, exhibiting a considerable scale in comparison to alternative datasets.",
    "Each problem is equipped with an optimal solution, the corresponding equation for obtaining the answer, and is enriched with a variety of templates.",
    "Tackling challenges within Ape210K necessitates multifaceted capabilities, encompassing natural language comprehension, mathematical reasoning, and common knowledge.",
    "• AQUA-RAT (Ling et al, 2017).",
    "The AQUA-RAT dataset consists of around 100K algebraic problems."
